premise_source_doc_sentence: Plot elements from `` The Hildebrand Rarity '' were used in the sixteenth Bond film , Licence to Kill  (  1989  )  , and the twenty-fourth Bond film Spectre references the title .
Spectre is the 24th instalment in the James Bond film series produced by Eon Productions for Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer and Columbia Pictures .
Spectre was estimated to have cost around $ 245 million , making it the most expensive Bond film and one of the most expensive films ever made .

The film follows Bond 's mission to find two NATO atomic bombs stolen by SPECTRE , which holds the world to ransom for # 100 million in diamonds , in exchange for not destroying an unspecified major city in either England or the United States  (  later revealed to be Miami  )  .
The film marks Spectre and Blofeld 's first appearance in an Eon Productions film since 1971 's Diamonds Are Forever with Christoph Waltz playing the organisation 's leader .
